# GitHub Copilot Instructions for {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Copilot reads this file automatically when generating code in this repository. It points at `AGENTS.md` at the repo root — the same content in one authoritative place.

## Read AGENTS.md first

Before suggesting code in this repository, read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root. It contains:

- The PowerShell version target.
- The function and script conventions.
- The output discipline (`Write-Verbose` over `Write-Host`).
- The dependency declaration rules.
- The secrets-handling rules.
- The green-before-done quality bar.

If any suggestion you make would violate those conventions, do not make the suggestion.

## Repository-specific shortcuts for Copilot

- Every function uses `[CmdletBinding()]` and typed `param()` with validation attributes.
- Every script starts with `Set-StrictMode -Version Latest` and `$ErrorActionPreference = 'Stop'`.
- Every credential comes from `Get-Secret`. There is no other path.
- Every new dependency is added to `requirements.psd1`. Do not `Install-Module` in a script body.
- Every new script in `scripts/` has a matching test file in `tests/`.

## What to avoid

- Windows PowerShell 5.1-only syntax. This project targets PS 7.4+.
- `Write-Host` in function bodies.
- Hardcoded paths, credentials, or environment-specific values.
- Aliases in committed code (`ls`, `?`, `%`, `gci`, `select`).
- `Invoke-Expression` on any input.
- Empty `catch` blocks.

## When asked to add a new script

1. Place the script in `scripts/`. Name it with PowerShell verb-noun casing (`Get-Foo`, `Set-Bar`, `Invoke-Baz`).
2. Add a matching test file in `tests/` named `<ScriptName>.Tests.ps1`.
3. Declare any new module dependencies in `requirements.psd1`.
4. Add a `## Added` entry under `[Unreleased]` in `CHANGELOG.md`.
5. Confirm PSScriptAnalyzer and Pester both report green locally before treating the task as done.
